{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"Wire the two-scope gate posture across all three gates, plumb resolution-class + diagnostic through the verdicts, define the exit-code-11 contract, own the shared-file integration, enforce never-certify structurally, and document the model.\n\n## Why\nThe three gates must share the systemic block-but-retryable posture while PRESERVING per-criterion fail-open, carry the `resolution_class` + `diagnostic` through the verdict/coverage so routing and troubleshooting both work, expose a distinct-but-grounded exit code, never sign a degraded result, and tell the human exactly what to do. This story is also the INTEGRATION OWNER for the shared seams the other children touch.\n\n## What\n- **Two-scope posture:** systemic failure -> block-but-retryable (exit 11, unsigned) for all three gates: make code-review match plan-review's existing systemic block; turn completion's fail-closed-as-FAIL into a distinct retryable exit (NOT a verification FAIL, which reads as \"your work is wrong\"). PRESERVE plan-review's per-criterion drop-and-continue fail-open (one flaky finder among N must not block the claim).\n- **Verdict-schema field (concrete):** add an optional `coverage.resolution_class` (enum of the 8 closed values) + `coverage.diagnostic` (sanitized object) to all three verdict schemas (`plan_review_verdict.schema.json`, `code_review_verdict.schema.json`, `completion_verdict.schema.json`). Absent field = a normal (non-degraded) verdict. **This story is the sole writer of these schema edits.**\n- **Exit-code-11 contract (concrete processing rule):** today a rate-limit/outage INDETERMINATE and a content-issue INDETERMINATE (refusal/truncation) both map to exit 2. The CLI/gate reads `coverage.resolution_class`: `WAIT_AND_RETRY`/`RETRY_NOW` -> exit 11 (\"transient — retry\"); every other non-null class -> exit 2 with that class's message; null -> existing PASS/BLOCK exit. Worked example: a 429-driven degraded plan-review carries `coverage.resolution_class = \"WAIT_AND_RETRY\"` -> `rebar review-plan` exits 11. Record an ADR for the exit-11 contract (one-way CLI-surface door).\n- **Never-sign structural guard (concrete):** in the attestation/`sign_manifest` path, assert `verdict.verdict == \"PASS\" and verdict.coverage.get(\"resolution_class\") is None` before signing; otherwise raise (a degraded/INDETERMINATE verdict is structurally unsignable — the illegal state cannot be represented as a signed attestation). Re-check the material fingerprint immediately before signing (retries + timeout widen the verify->sign window; avoid attesting against drifted state). Keep verify strictly OUTSIDE the write lock (`transition_close.py` current ordering preserved).\n- **Integration ownership (shared files):** `src/rebar/llm/runner.py` is modified by five children (30ff, 95a5, fd1d, 978d, 9a82) at distinct but adjacent seams (except-seam classification; transport wiring at model construction; timeout/step-cap wiring; output validation; construction-time capability check), and `config.py`/`_config_schema.py`/the verdict schemas/docs by several. This story lands LAST (merge order 0->1->{2,3,4,5}->6), owns the final `runner.py` reconciliation, and is the single-source-of-truth for the config namespace, the verdict-schema edits, and the taxonomy/retry/timeout docs. Per-child config-key docs defer to the consolidated doc here. Each contributing child names its exact `runner.py` seam in its description to keep the merges non-overlapping.\n- Per-class actionable messages; the MCP error shape; exit code 11. Docs + ADRs (exit-11, diagnostic-sanitization, deferred async watchdog, scope-vs-title).\n\n## Scope\n- `gate_dispatch.py` wiring; `transition_close.py` (preserve verify-outside-lock ordering + add pre-sign fingerprint re-check); the verdict JSON schemas; `docs/` + `docs/adr/`.\n- NOT in scope: removing or weakening per-criterion fail-open (must be preserved).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] All three gates: a systemic failure -> block-but-retryable, exit 11 for retryable classes (else exit 2), unsigned, with a class-specific actionable message; exit-code mapping is driven by `coverage.resolution_class` and covered by tests.\n- [ ] Per-criterion fail-open is preserved (a single flaky unit among N does not block; regression test).\n- [ ] `resolution_class` + sanitized `diagnostic` are plumbed through the verdict schemas + `coverage` + the session log; this story is the only writer of the schema change.\n- [ ] The structural never-sign guard rejects signing any degraded/INDETERMINATE verdict; the material fingerprint is re-checked before signing.\n- [ ] Verify remains outside the write lock (ordering preserved; asserted).\n- [ ] ADRs recorded (exit-11 contract, diagnostic sanitization, deferred async watchdog, scope-vs-title); consolidated docs updated; `make test`/`make lint`/`make typecheck` green.\n\nFiles: `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py`, `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py`, `src/rebar/schemas/*.schema.json`, `src/rebar/llm/runner.py` (final shared-seam reconciliation), the attestation/`sign_manifest` path, `docs/`, `docs/adr/`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783560014936844001,"uuid":"23ef96b6-6045-40fc-8219-14d335c34570"}